---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Navbar from '../../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Upscaler Studio | EDITH Dev Studio"
  description="Discover Upscaler Studio, a local AI upscaling tool for Windows by EDITH Dev Studio."
>
  <Navbar />

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-bg-orb orb-1"></div>
    <div class="hero-bg-orb orb-2"></div>

    <div class="container hero-grid">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Upscaler Studio · by EDITH Dev Studio</p>
        <h1>Local AI upscaling for Windows.</h1>
        <p class="hero-copy">
          Upscaler Studio is being shaped as a premium Windows-first desktop tool for image and video upscaling,
          built around local processing, batch workflows, compare tools, history, and a stronger product experience.
        </p>

        <div class="cta-row">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/download">Download trial</a>
          <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/pricing">View pricing</a>
        </div>

        <div class="hero-stats">
          <div>
            <strong>Local-first</strong>
            <span>Processing direction</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <strong>Image + Video</strong>
            <span>One product surface</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <strong>Batch-ready</strong>
            <span>Workflow focus</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="hero-card premium-panel float-panel">
        <div class="hero-appbar">
          <span></span><span></span><span></span>
        </div>
        <div class="preview-shell">
          <div class="preview-block low">Input preview</div>
          <div class="process-card">
            <div class="process-head">
              <strong>AI preset active</strong>
              <small>Model recommendation direction</small>
            </div>
            <div class="bar"><i></i></div>
          </div>
          <div class="preview-block high">Enhanced output</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Why it matters</p>
      <h2>A real product direction, not a disposable utility.</h2>
      <div class="cards three">
        <article class="card premium-panel">
          <h3>Premium desktop positioning</h3>
          <p>
            The goal is a serious Windows-first product with stronger UX, clearer packaging, and a better commercial surface.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="card premium-panel">
          <h3>Local processing focus</h3>
          <p>
            Upscaler Studio is positioned around local control, stronger privacy posture, and reduced dependence on cloud workflows.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="card premium-panel">
          <h3>Workflow-oriented design</h3>
          <p>
            Compare, history, queueing, and guided processing direction aim to make the tool feel more complete and professional.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Core product direction</p>
      <h2>What Upscaler Studio is designed to offer.</h2>
      <div class="cards three">
        <article class="card premium-panel">
          <h3>Image and video workflows</h3>
          <p>One product identity built around both still-image enhancement and video-oriented processing direction.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card premium-panel">
          <h3>Batch and review flow</h3>
          <p>Queue-based processing, result review, compare direction, and history visibility for more consistent work.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card premium-panel">
          <h3>Windows-first product experience</h3>
          <p>A desktop product feel that aims higher than a typical wrapper around command-line tools.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container cta-panel premium-panel glow-border">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Launch path</p>
        <h2>Start with a trial. Upgrade when the product proves itself.</h2>
        <p>
          The current go-to-market direction is a simple, premium launch model: a trial path plus a single clear paid license.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="cta-stack">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/download">Download trial</a>
        <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/pricing">Pricing</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
